ing Darius I. This study reconstructs the genesis and development of these two prophetic books over a period of several centuries and integrates their various revisions into the historical context of the theology of ancient Judaism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAltes Testament /Redaktionsgeschichte. 4aDodekapropheton. 4aHaggai. 4aSacharja. 4aZwölfprophetenbuch. 70(DE-588)4059416-60(DE-627)10439403X0(DE-576)209130709aTempel2gnd 70(DE-588)4062877-20(DE-627)1048262150(DE-576)209146451aVerheißung2gnd 70(DE-588)4063790-60(DE-627)1041066030(DE-576)209150475aVolk2gnd 70(DE-588)4114051-50(DE-627)1058250180(DE-576)20948151XaIntertextualität2gnd 70(DE-588)4136148-90(DE-627)1042974250(DE-576)209666749aReinheit2gnd 70(DE-588)4175942-40(DE-627)1053602280(DE-576)209967250aProphet2gnd 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aBook of the Twelve Prophets.  aDodekapropheton.  aHaggai.  aMinor Prophets.  aOld Testament.  aRedaction History.  aZechariah.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2010z9783110233544oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE/RELIGIONSWISS./JUDAISTIK  2010z9783110233643oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311022486340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311022487040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110224870423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110224870/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2010  aZDB-23-DGGb2010  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2